An unusually open and unique image of Karel Gott in the feature-length documentary film by Olga Špátová
This unique film from the workshop of Olga Špátová will premiere in Czech cinemas in the spring of next year.
"In the middle of September last year, Ivanka and Karel Gott called me and asked me if I would make a documentary about his life with Karel again after ten years. I didn't hesitate for a minute! Filming with a person who has lasted more than half a century at the forefront of Czech culture thanks to his exceptional singing talent, artistic humility and immeasurable hard work, it was and is a great honor for me. I accepted the challenge to make a feature-length documentary film about Karl Gott, who has brought joy to three generations of listeners with his art, as a commitment to this legendary singer, " director Olga Špátová describes her feelings.
Thanks to a quick arrangement and agreement, the first day of filming took place already on October 22 last year, and the last shots with Karl Gott were filmed a few days ago. The goal was and is absolutely clear - to capture authentically Karel Gott as a phenomenal singer who gives himself to his fans, as a painter, but at the same time a loving husband and father of his children. A man who for sixty years has been giving joy to several generations with his songs, not only in our country, but also in Europe, and actually all over the world. A man who has written himself into the hearts and souls of his listeners by simply being.
The film is not intended to be a parade of the indisputable fame of Karel Gott and his achievements. "That's why it's not even possible to compare my previous film Phenomén Gott with this current one. Everyone is different. At least because we filmed them in a different stage of Karl Gott's life, and this is very evident in his personal, even intimate confession that he gave us and which confirmed to all of us what a legend we have the opportunity to work with and spend time with, which is truly indescribable," adds Olga Špátová.
The creators captured Karel Gott during his performances, during meetings with his fans here and in Hamburg, but especially in his home environment, whether in Prague, at a cottage in Bohemian Switzerland, in the village where he spent his childhood, and in other places that she played an important role in his life. Thanks to Karel Gott's frank openness, the film will be completely authentic and unique.
"Olga has a great gift for filming with her close team in such a way that we often let ourselves be carried away by the spontaneous atmosphere and naturally let her into our privacy, thanks to which I talked about relatively intimate topics. With my husband, cameraman Jan Malíř, I actually they have become part of our family. We originally wanted to release the film in 2019, when I celebrated my life anniversary. But since I had another beautiful summer with my family, I wanted us to shoot as long as possible. Well, and since 2019 I was everywhere , my wish was for it to be released in the spring of next year. This documentary film is a thank you to my supporters and everyone who supported and accompanied me in my profession," says Karel Gott himself about the film.
