Babiš entered politics with the promise that he would "fix things". In terms of meaningful investments and acceleration of cumbersome bureaucratic procedures, not much has happened yet. Although an amendment to the Act on accelerating the construction of transport infrastructure has been in effect since 2018, we will have to wait for more extensive positive effects, for example easier expropriation of land. And the new construction law, approved by the government, which is supposed to reduce the current average length of the construction procedure from 5.4 years to one year, will, if we're lucky, start to apply from 2021. But many people probably wouldn't bet on it .
