Declaration of the end of the right in the lower house, or what kind of "right-wing" coalition of ODS, TOP 09, STAN and KDU?
Recently, there have been reports in the media and commentaries about the upcoming coalition of the mentioned parties. Many are applauding that the "right" is finally getting together, but I rather wonder why these parties still call themselves right-wing.
Leaving aside the new Tricolor movement, the Czech Chamber of Deputies no longer has a real right-wing party. And it doesn't matter how the given subjects label themselves or what label the mainstream media parrots. The ODS is hardly centrist in its average of the top politicians of this party, TOP 09 is clearly the party of the urban pseudo-liberal left (which is ashamed of its leftism and thus hypocritically describes itself as conservative or even right-wing). STAN is a party that basically merges with TOP 09 in terms of its concept, ideology and voter targeting (the reason for its existence is simply not clear to me). And the KDU even labels itself as centrist for a long time - however, their political compass is much more to the left than they say.
Do you feel that I have taken everyone out of the same water? No, I am based on the real political steps of these parties. If I consider myself a classically liberal right-wing voter, the highest value for me is the freedom of the individual, the free market and minimal interference by the state in the lives of individuals and the economy. How do these parties fulfill this general right-wing assumption? How many laws cutting people's liberties with the salami method, raising taxes, confirming new regulations and increasing surveillance, increasing attachment to the socialist EU or promoting environmental and gender madness have they supported in recent years? A lot, really a lot. Not their labels, but their actions identify them. These parties, despite all kinds of declarations or partial concessions, want to strengthen the role of the state in our lives. And that has nothing to do with right-wingness.
I would not be at all surprised by the coalition cooperation of TOP 09, STAN and KDU, they simply belong together on the political map and, with the exception of Christian or, on the contrary, homosexual and gender aspects, I do not see any obvious difference in them for the voters in terms of the influence of the state on their lives. However, the ODS has long been portrayed as "the only right-wing party" and by associating with these three entities, it already openly reveals its true political affiliation.
By the way, when I mentioned the stickers briefly. Have you noticed how often all these parties cheaply label critics of dirigisme and socialism coming from the European Union as pro-Russian agents? Can't they or just don't want to understand that there are many people who do not smell Eurosocialism and growing unfreedom as strongly as the authoritarian regime in Russia? Are they hiding their complete incompetence in argumentation and their unreasonable or blind adoration of European Union conditions?
In short, it is possible that in the Czech Republic other than centrist politics no longer have a chance of greater success. Maybe voters really want this kind of merger. Maybe they want center-left politics under the guise of "right-wing" because they are ashamed of their political beliefs (or can't even identify them). I don't know. But I am definitely not one of those voters.
