When choosing a red lipstick, you should first determine whether you are a warm or cool type. Try a simple test - look at the veins on your wrist. If they are blue, you are a cold type, if they are green, then you are a warm type. When choosing a new red lipstick, the first thing to do is sort it by undertone. Pay attention to the texture in the next one.
If you belong to women with a cold undertone, then purple, plum, cherry or mauve lipsticks are suitable for you.
If you fall into the warm skin undertone category, choose such lipsticks as well. You can recognize them by the fact that they gravitate towards orange, coral, gold or brown highlights.
You may find that some veins appear green and others appear blue. In that case, congratulations - you don't have to look at the undertone and you can only focus on your color preferences.
