Designed for business users
1. Functional specification – a detailed description of all the business functionalities of the Application with an emphasis on business vocabulary (the business user must understand what and how the delivered Application enables automation), description of the appearance of all Application screens (description of individual control elements and functionalities that ensure data processing) and description of all print outputs of the Application, with a definition of their appearance, content, formatting (description of documents, statements and print reports)
2. Description of business processes – a document that complements the Functional Specification – a detailed description of individual life situations of the Application with an emphasis on business vocabulary (the business user must understand how the Application works in all situations it automates)
3. Description of business roles - a document that complements the Functional Specification - description of business/user roles of the Application, including a description of their mapping to business processes (the business user must understand which type of user performs the relevant processes and know how the attributes of the graphical user interface are mapped to individual business roles)
4. Description of parameterization – a document that complements the Functional Specification – description of Application parameterization (e.g. description of how to configure products, description of accounting regulation settings, description of codebook configuration, description of algorithm configuration, ...) with an emphasis on the exact values of individual parameters and a description of the manifestation changes to the relevant parameter value in the processing of the Application (the business user must understand and know exactly how the Application is parameterized and how it reacts to individual parameter values in order to be able to make any changes as needed in productive operation), a description of the transfer of the parameter configuration from the test environment to the production environment (The customer must be able to consistently transfer the "tested" parameter configuration from the environment where they prepare it to the production environment)
5. Description of UAT scenarios – UAT test scenarios that are part of the Acceptance Procedure
Designed for the application architect/systems integrator
1. Description of data interfaces – a document that supplements the Functional Specification – a precise description of the data interfaces that the Application makes available to other systems, including a description of the mechanism for calling them, the method of validation of individual data items (type, value restrictions, obligation, ...), error report, description of necessary performance settings (speed of data processing/provision, number of calls per time, ...), description of security settings (method of authentication and authorization of the calling counterparty)
2. Description of third-party interfaces – a document that supplements the Functional Specification – a precise description of the services and interfaces of third-party systems that the Application uses/calls during its operation (exact description of the data structure of the service, frequency of calls over time, performance settings, ...) , description of error messages, description of security settings (similar content as in the previous part)
3. Description of performance parameters - a document that supplements the Functional Specification - description of performance criteria/parameters to be met by the Application (e.g. speed of response to opening the screen, generation of print output, number of parallel logged-in users, maximum duration of closing or export, .. .)
Designed for safety
1. Description of security features – a document in .docx or .pdf format that supplements the Functional Specification – a precise description of the security algorithms, a description of the mechanism of user roles and control of the execution of operations by individual users, a description of the mechanism of data cancellation in the event of an error, a description of the mechanism of auditing performed operations, description of the application of GDPR requirements, description of the protection of system users and the mechanism of their access to data in the Application, description of logging of changes, description of the audit of the authorization of operations, or description of other features and parameters of the Application related to security and security standards
