Annex No. 9 / Acceptance procedure
The items below are for inspiration only. This appendix must be formulated precisely and comprehensively by the project manager.
Delivery of the Upgrade
Acceptance criteria for the Upgrade Delivery to start the Acceptance Procedure
Delivery of an incremental version of those parts of the Application in the form of executable codes that are affected by the Upgrade
Delivery of the current version of the Functional Specifications and Documentation of those parts of the Application that are affected by the Upgrade
Successful implementation of the installation of the Upgrade on the UAT environment according to the installation procedure, while the installation is performed by the Customer's employee with the assistance of the Contractor's employees
Successful demonstration of Changes and Incidents included in the Upgrade, while the demonstration will be performed by the Contractor's employees and will be marked as successful if 80% of the demonstrated functionality runs without problems
Acceptance criteria for the Upgrade Delivery for the execution of the Acceptance Procedure
Successful completion of the UAT (by executing all relevant test scenarios), whereby the UATs are completed as successful if the delivered Upgrade contains at most the following number of unclosed Incidents:
TA category incident: 0 (none)
incident category TB: 3 (three)
Incident category TC: 10 (ten)
Successful execution of business critical scenarios in a UAT environment, with no business critical scenario reporting a TA, TB or TC Incident
The acceptance procedure of the Upgrade Delivery can be terminated even if the number of unresolved Incidents from the UAT environment at one time, which are defects of the Application or Documentation, reaches or exceeds the following number of unresolved Incidents:
TA category incident: 5 (five)
incident category TB: 10 (ten)
Incident category TC: 30 (thirty)
Patch delivery
Acceptance Criteria for Patch Delivery
Delivery of an incremental version of those portions of the Application in the form of executable codes that are affected by the Patch
Delivery of the current version of the Functional Specifications and Documentation of those parts of the Application that are affected by the Patch, and if it is expedient to resolve the Incident/s, these parts can also be delivered in the next Upgrade
Successful verification of the resolution of the Incident/Incidents included in the Patch, where the Patch must not report any Incidents
If the Patch has not resolved all the Incidents included in it, it is up to the Customer to mark the Acceptance Procedure as successful
