Appendix 12 / Safety rules
1. Definition of terms
1.1 For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases have the meanings set out below:
Security Incident means any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
Information asset means any information, processes, hardware or software components that (1) support the Authorized Entity's business activities, or (2) have value to the Authorized Entity, or (3) the disclosure, unauthorized alteration, or unavailability of which has a negative impact on the Authorized Entity .
The Contractor's persons means persons who are directly or indirectly involved in the fulfillment of the subject matter of this Agreement, including persons of the Contractor's subcontractors.
The environment of the Authorized Entity means the premises in which the Authorized Entity carries out its business activities and the information and communication systems that the Authorized Entity uses and which contain Information Assets.
2. Personal security
2.1 None of the Contractor's Persons:
2.1.1 does not have a criminal record;
2.1.2 has not been convicted of an intentional crime in the past and is not being prosecuted at the time of the fulfillment of the subject of this Agreement,
2.2 If the Contractor discovers non-compliance with the above-mentioned rules among the Contractor's Persons, he must immediately inform the Customer of this. The Client is entitled to demand that such a person no longer participates in the implementation of the works resulting from the subject of this Agreement, either directly or indirectly, and is entitled to demand that the Contractor provide adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor shall provide the Customer with a complete name list of the Contractor's Persons. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Customer of changes in the personnel security for the performance of this Agreement in advance.
2.4 Persons of the Contractor:
2.4.1 must be familiar with these safety rules,
2.4.2 they have all the necessary tests and certifications that result from the law or the requirements of the regulator for the type of work they are to perform in connection with the performance of this Agreement,
2.4.3 The Contractor regularly provides training in the areas of information security.
2.5 The Contractor's Persons may not enter the Environment of the Authorized Entity under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, flammables, weapons, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substances threatening human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 Access of the Contractor's Persons to the Environment of the Authorized Entity is permitted only if their presence is necessary for the performance of work duties arising from this Agreement.
3.2 The Contractor's personnel are always accompanied by the Customer's responsible employee in the Authorized Entity's Environment.
3.3 Free movement of the Contractor's Persons in the Authorized Entity's Environment is permitted only if the person in question has been issued a personal access card. The Contractor may not further lend the access card to third parties or enable third parties to access the Authorized Entity's Environment.
3.4 In case of loss of the access card or in case of suspicion of loss of the access card, the Contractor is obliged to inform the Customer immediately.
3.5 Without undue delay after the completion of the work resulting from this Agreement or after the termination of this Agreement, or if further physical access of the Contractor's Persons to the Authorized Entity's Environment is no longer necessary, the Client shall ensure that all the Contractor's Persons return the loaned access cards to the Client.
3.6 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not remove any Information Assets from the Environment of the Authorized Entity via a storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of the Contractor's Persons in the Environment of the Authorized Entity
4.1 The Contractor's persons are assigned only accounts that enable clear identification of the user and only with such authorizations as they absolutely need to fulfill their work duties arising from this Agreement.
4.2 The Contractor performs normal work tasks under non-privileged accounts, using accounts with administrator rights only in necessary cases.
4.3 The Contractor's persons may not access the Internet if they work under an account with administrator privileges or with applications that are launched under administrator privileges.
4.4 Inactive accounts of the Contractor's Persons are proactively reported by the Contractor to the Customer.
4.5 Shared accounts are used by the Contractor only with the prior written consent of the Customer.
4.6 In the event of password disclosure or in the event of suspicion of password disclosure, the Contractor must immediately ensure that the password is changed or blocked.
5. Handling of certificates
5.1 Access to the certificates (both logical and physical) will be allowed only to those of the Contractor for whom this access is necessary for the performance of their work duties.
5.2 Without the written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not provide or make the certificates available to third parties.
5.3 After their installation, certificates can only be stored in a secure storage in places where their storage is necessary for the fulfillment of this Agreement, and all other copies will be destroyed in a way that makes it impossible to restore them again.
5.4 If possible, the private key of the certificate must be set as non-exportable. The private key of the certificate must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in an unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to immediately inform the Customer of the loss or suspected loss of confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Handling of Information Assets
6.1 Work with Information Assets is limited only to places that exclude the observation of sensitive information by unauthorized persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in public transport, in public places and in places where there is a risk of surveillance from industrial cameras.
6.2 Upon completion of the work resulting from this Agreement, the Contractor shall without undue delay return or remove all Information assets stored in the Contractor's environment, if the retention of this information is not required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The deletion of Information Assets must be done in a way that makes it impossible to recover them.
6.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not provide access to the Information Assets to any third parties who are not authorized to participate in the performance of this Agreement.
6.4 The Contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer technology on which the Information Assets are stored, processed or transmitted. In connection with the Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the Contractor's environment:
6.4.1 tools are used to encrypt disks, folders and/or files, so that unauthorized access to Information Assets is excluded,
6.4.2 tools are used for detection and removal of malicious code with regular updating of the database of signatures of malicious code with a frequency not exceeding one week, and corresponding processes of supervision, logging and response to a positive finding of malicious code are set,
6.4.3 processes for updating security patches of software components are defined, set, executed and monitored at an interval not exceeding one month from the release of patches,
6.4.4 the Internet environment is separated by a firewall, which is connected to supervision, and the Contractor's Persons use only an encrypted VPN connection during remote access to prevent unauthorized interception and alteration of transmitted communication.
6.5 If Information Assets are transferred by the Contractor outside the premises of the Authorized Entity, the Contractor is obliged to consistently take care of the physical security of these assets and to keep these Information Assets under supervision at all times. The contractor is obliged to comply with the safety and operating instructions of the manufacturer of the hardware on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Work in the Environment of the Authorized Entity
7.1 The Contractor is obliged to familiarize himself with and act in accordance with the standard for the classification of Information Assets, if provided by the Customer.
7.2 For hardware that is owned and managed by the Customer or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved by the Customer in advance, the Contractor may not make changes to the configuration of this hardware not approved by the Customer. In particular, the Contractor may not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each such installed hardware, a security patch application process must be explicitly and formally established, including the responsibilities of the roles within the process.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not install or run any software not previously approved by the Customer.
7.4 Without the written consent of the Customer, the Contractor is not authorized to perform any physical or logical security testing or any type of control mechanisms of the Authorized Entity.
7.5 The contractor may not manipulate the audit records in any way.
7.6 The Contractor's personnel are not authorized to work with software, hardware or data content that is not directly related to the performance of this Agreement.
7.7 The Contractor's persons may not carry out any activities that harm other natural or legal persons, including sending unsolicited emails, sending fraudulent emails, distributing malicious code or participating in attacks with the aim of disabling the availability of services.
7.8 The Customer logs all steps taken by the Contractor's Personnel and keeps a record of them for a period of 3 years.
7.9 Without the written consent of the Customer, the Contractor's Persons may not connect their own memory devices to any computing equipment of the Authorized Entity.
7.10 During the period of physical absence, the Contractor's Persons are obliged to ensure:
7.10.1 cleanliness and order so that the workplace can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logical locking of access to Information Assets so that unauthorized access to these Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor's personnel are not authorized to install devices enabling remote listening or to make any audio or video recording.
8. Crisis management
8.1 The Contractor's persons are obliged to the highest possible extent to prevent the occurrence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury or damage to the property of the Authorized Person could occur.
8.2 In the event of a crisis situation, the Contractor's Person who is physically present at the scene of the event is obliged, without exception or delay, to comply with the regulations and directives valid in the given location and to obey instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to exercise.
8.3 In the case of crisis management, the Contractor's Person is obliged to immediately obey the instructions of the Customer's crisis manager.
9. Reporting of Security Incidents
9.1 If the Contractor identifies a security incident, he is obliged to immediately report it to the tool https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (phone: +420 221 710 911).
