3. Date of execution of the Work / The Work will be performed by the Contractor by the date specified in the Change Documentation.
4. Price / For properly executed Work, the Customer shall pay the Contractor the Price, which is stated in the Change Documentation (hereinafter referred to as the "Price").
5. Payment of the Price / The Customer shall pay the Price to the Contractor upon acceptance of the Work, in accordance with the SLA.
6. Other costs for the execution of the Work / The price includes all costs incurred by the Contractor in connection with the execution of the Work. The price also includes expenses for the performance of third parties used by the Contractor in the production of the Work, in particular the costs of the performance of subcontractors, including authors and other external licensors, etc.
7. Default interest / If the Customer does not pay the Price within the due date, the Customer shall pay to the Contractor a default interest of 0.05% of the amount with which the Customer is in arrears for each day of delay. If the Customer does not pay the Price or part of it due to a claim due to defects in the Work, it is not in arrears.
8. Execution of the Work / Procedures in accordance with the SLA will be used to execute the Work.
9. Acceptance procedure / The place of delivery and acceptance of the Work is the Customer's registered office. The Acceptance Procedure shall be used to accept the Work in accordance with the SLA.
10. Defects in the Work / The Work has a defect if it does not have the properties specified by this Agreement and the Change Documentation.
11. Obligation to exchange information / The parties shall exchange all information necessary for the performance of this Agreement.
12. Instructions / If the Customer issues a written instruction aimed at fulfilling the subject of this Agreement and if such instruction does not conflict with the legitimate interests of the Parties, the Contractor shall comply with such instruction. The Contractor shall notify the Customer of the inappropriateness of his instructions without undue delay after such inappropriate instruction is delivered to the Contractor. If it is not possible to issue the necessary instruction in time, the Contractor will act conscientiously at his own discretion and with knowledge of the anticipated interests of the Client.
13. Duty to cooperate / For the purpose of making the Work, the Customer shall provide the Contractor with all cooperation that can reasonably be required of him. If the Customer does not provide cooperation and, as a result, there is a delay in the completion of the Work, the delivery period is extended by the period during which the Customer did not provide cooperation.
14. Compliance of the Work with legal regulations / The Work will be produced by the Contractor in such a way that it corresponds to the generally binding legal regulations of the Czech Republic and this Agreement. The work must not infringe any third party intellectual property right, patent protection, trademark, copyright or trade secret.
