The Epistles of Peter of Blois will also be exhibited, where the opening miniature H (enrico) depicts a half-figure of the English king Henry II. The author of the decoration is most likely the Master of Samson's History, who, next to the two volumes of the Bible of Wenceslas IV. he also participated in the decoration of a number of other manuscripts. Visitors will also see a collection of Latin treatises by John Wycliffe from around 1411 to 1414.
