The opening of Pumpkin World delayed the ripening of pumpkins
Nová Ves u Leštiny (Havlíčkobrod Region) - The estate in Nová Ves u Leštiny in the Havlíčkobrod region opened Pumpkin World today for more than a month. Huge orange pyramids dominate the decorations made of thousands of freshly harvested pumpkins. The fall event, which is becoming a tradition, starts a week later this year, because the pumpkins in the Pipk family's seven hectares of fields have matured longer. There are still a lot of them in the field, Jaroslava Pipková told ČTK today.
The Pipks grow many kinds of pumpkins, but the weather hasn't been kind to them in the last two years. This year's harvest was delayed and some varieties did not come out. "As usual, we have enough orange pumpkins for Halloween, but some varieties for connoisseurs did not succeed," said Pipková. Nevertheless, you can choose from several types at the farm, from the already mentioned large pumpkins suitable for carving and gouging decorations, to cooking Hokkaido or elongated "spaghetti" pumpkins, to decorative pumpkins of various colors and shapes.
Growing pumpkins is hard work. Farmers dig up the plants by hand and harvest their fruits, cutting the pumpkin from the stem with scissors. Pumpkin World has been open to Pipko regularly since 2010, previous editions have attracted thousands of people. Decorations made of pumpkins are complemented by attractions made of straw or a maze made of logs. Visitors will also see animals raised on the farm. It will be open daily until November 3.
Details about the event are on the farm's website, where the growers also offer some recipes for pumpkin dishes, such as pumpkin muffins or juice. The visitors themselves tell them about other options for preparing pumpkin in the kitchen. "A lot of cooks have tried their recipes, and we get inspired," said Pipková. She pointed out that some housewives also pickle pumpkins like pickles.
