The researchers are looking for toddlers with a congenital defect, so-called ankle valgus, for their study
Ankle valgus is a congenital defect that affects five to ten percent of children. It is usually treated with intensive exercise. Scientists are trying to help these children even more, so they have developed special shoes that should significantly speed up the treatment.
"We have two prototypes of shoes that will be worn by healthy children and children with a diagnosis in order to map the effect in both groups. At the same time, participating in the research will not have any risks for the children and the measurement will be completely painless," explains Marta Gimunová, head of research from the Faculty of Sports Studies HIM.
Parents of both groups of children can apply for the study via the website, where a registration form and all information are available.
The researchers are looking for fifty children with the diagnosis and fifty healthy children. Of each group, half will always wear medical shoes and half will not.
"The moment when parents should register their child is the moment when they start taking their first independent steps, typically they start, for example, the furniture that they are holding on to when trying to walk. Participation in the research involves three measurements within seven months of the child's first steps , each lasting about 20 minutes, for half of the participants it also includes wearing the tested shoes," points out Gimunová.
